(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- AI: The main topic being studied, understood here as artificial intelligence allows) Tj
T*
(computers to perform tasks that appear to require human intelligence.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: pattern) Tj
T*
(recognition, learning from data, and responsible use.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as describing) Tj
T*
(how a recommendation system works.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example assuming AI) Tj
T*
(always understands information like a person.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of AI: pattern recognition, learning from data, and) Tj
T*
(responsible use.) Tj
T*
(- Assuming AI always understands information like a person.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising AI without checking whether the method matches the question being asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Quick Check) Tj
T*
(- In your own words, what does AI mean in Computer Science?) Tj
T*
